                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> A convention made <origDate notBefore="1314-07-08" notAfter="1315-07-07">8 Ed. II</origDate>, on the feast of St. Matthew the apostle,
               between the <orgName key="org_109067">abbot and convent of Oseney</orgName> of the one part, and
               <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> le <surname>Clerke</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_109308">Hampton Gay</placeName>
                        </persName> 
               of the other part, viz. that the abbot and convent grant to the said Gilbert two acres of arable land 
               in the fields of <placeName key="place_109308">Hampton</placeName>, of which 3 half/acres lie in 
               <placeName type="minor">Smalefarlong</placeName> and half an acre in 
               <placeName type="minor">Edinannaforlong</placeName> between the path of the land of
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Grondweye</surname>
                        </persName>. 
               . </p>
